# Semantic Reconstruction Control Plane — bounded project intent kernel.

goal goal.semctx.reconstructive-control
  statement: Semctx must reconstruct intent across code and architecture while keeping every conclusion traceable to explicit evidence.
  status: declared
  provenance: author
  appliesAtLevel: 6
  tag: control-plane
  tag: critical

goal goal.semctx.typed-refinement-intent
  statement: Maintainers can trace a governing goal to exact observed code hunks and lift those observations back without inventing semantic authority.
  status: declared
  provenance: author
  appliesAtLevel: 5
  tag: control-plane
  tag: refinement

invariant invariant.semctx.plane-separation
  statement: Derived repository facts, authored semantic intent, and migration control state remain distinct typed planes.
  status: declared
  provenance: author
  appliesAtLevel: 4
  serves: goal.semctx.reconstructive-control
  file: docs/architecture/semantic-layer-v1.md
  tag: critical

invariant invariant.semctx.fail-closed-control
  statement: Missing targets, deltas, runtime observations, or sufficient proofs must block cutover and deletion.
  status: declared
  provenance: author
  appliesAtLevel: 4
  serves: goal.semctx.reconstructive-control
  tag: critical

decision decision.semctx.read-only-plane-c
  statement: Plane C is an additive read-only control surface until replay and shadow evidence justify a separate executor.
  status: declared
  provenance: author
  appliesAtLevel: 4
  justifies: invariant.semctx.plane-separation
  justifies: invariant.semctx.fail-closed-control
  tag: architecture

decision decision.semctx.typed-refinement-policy
  statement: Refinement traversal admits only adjacent typed relations with explicit evidence and keeps constraints and proofs outside the load-bearing path.
  status: declared
  provenance: author
  appliesAtLevel: 3
  tag: control-plane
  tag: refinement

decision decision.semctx.control-engine-boundary
  statement: The control engine projects and traverses the read-only Plane-C overlay without constructing changes or execution envelopes.
  status: declared
  provenance: author
  appliesAtLevel: 2
  tag: architecture
  tag: read-only

assumption assumption.semctx.index-is-current
  statement: A coordinate trace is useful only when the repository index represents the requested commit.
  status: assumed
  provenance: author
  appliesAtLevel: 4
  tag: freshness

unknown unknown.semctx.runtime-dependencies
  statement: Static repository facts cannot prove that a legacy path has no runtime consumers.
  status: declared
  provenance: author
  appliesAtLevel: 4
  tag: deletion

evidence proof.semctx.baseline-suite
  statement: Before Plane C implementation, typecheck and 195 repository tests passed on the working baseline.
  status: tested
  provenance: author
  appliesAtLevel: 1
  tag: regression-baseline

evidence proof.semctx.typed-refinement-contract
  statement: Versioned schemas and tests define the exact typed refinement contract shared by the semantic DSL and control engine.
  status: tested
  provenance: author
  appliesAtLevel: 1
  file: packages/control-engine/test/l6-l0-refinement-round-trip.test.ts
  tag: refinement
  tag: test

change change.semctx.control-plane-mvp
  statement: Add deterministic semantic coordinates, architecture delta planning, and fail-closed proof authorization without execution authority.
  status: active
  provenance: author
  appliesAtLevel: 1
  serves: goal.semctx.reconstructive-control
  preserves:
    - invariant.semctx.plane-separation
    - invariant.semctx.fail-closed-control
  requires: proof.semctx.baseline-suite
  unknown: unknown.semctx.runtime-dependencies
  file: docs/architecture/semantic-layer-v1.md
  tag: control-plane
  tag: shadow-first

